name: parker-river-national-wildlife-refuge-narrative-report-september-october-november-and-dece-44342
notes: This narrative report for Parker River National Wildlife Refuge outlines Refuge accomplishments from September through December of 1946. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions, water conditions, and food and cover during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, predators, and rodents- is also covered. The public relations section of the report describes Refuge visitors. N-R forms are attached.
